cerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without cadence the addendum carries no operational commitment.","id":"ADDENDA-002-s1-0","recommendation":"State the cadence: e.g., 'Vendor shall maintain a current SOC 2 Type II report renewed annually.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-sp-800-53-consensus-practice-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST SP 800-53 (consensus practice)","source_url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final"}],"title":"Security-review cadence missing"},{"description":"No notification window for security incidents (e.g., 48 hours, 72 hours) was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Vague 'prompt' / 'without undue delay' language is unenforceable; regulated parties (HIPAA, GDPR) require specific windows.","id":"ADDENDA-004-s1-0","recommendation":"Specify a window: e.g., 'Vendor shall notify Customer within 48 hours of confirming a security incident affecting Customer Data.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-sp-800-53-consensus-practice-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST SP 800-53 (consensus practice)","source_url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final"}],"title":"Incident-response notification window missing"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a governing-law clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no governing-law clause)"},"explanation":"A governing-law clause picks the legal system that interprets the contract. Without it, courts apply conflict-of-laws rules, which may produce unexpected results.","id":"CHOICE-001-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No governing-law clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not allocate ownership of intellectual property.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no IP-ownership clause)"},"explanation":"Without an IP-ownership clause, default copyright and patent rules apply: under 17 U.S.C. § 201, copyright vests in the author/employee unless work-for-hire or assignment applies.","id":"IPDATA-001-s1-0","rule_id":"IPDATA-001","rule_version":"1.1.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-17-usc-101","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 101 — Definitions (work made for hire)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/101"},{"id":"stat-17-usc-201","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"17 U.S.C. § 201","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/17/201"}],"title":"No IP-ownership clause detected"},{"description":"Neither 'indemnify' nor 'hold harmless' appears in the document.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no indemnification language)"},"explanation":"Most commercial contracts allocate risk through an indemnification clause. The absence leaves the parties to default tort and contract law for any third-party claims.","id":"RISK-001-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-001","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No indemnification clause detected"},{"description":"Vaulytica did not find a limitation-of-liability clause.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no LoL clause)"},"explanation":"Without a limitation-of-liability clause, exposure is bounded only by what the parties can prove in damages. Most commercial contracts cap liability.","id":"RISK-005-s1-0","rule_id":"RISK-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No limitation-of-liability clause detected"},{"description":"Used but not defined: All Customer Data, Customer Data, Vulnerability Management.","document_position":1386,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1403,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1386,"text":"All Customer Data"},"explanation":"Title-Case phrases in a contract usually signal a defined term. When they aren't defined, readers must guess at the intended meaning. Either define them or use lowercase if the term is intended in its ordinary sense.","id":"STRUCT-006-s1-1386","recommendation":"Add a definition for each genuinely defined term, or change the casing if the phrase is being used in its ordinary sense.","rule_id":"STRUCT-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"Undefined Title-Case terms: 3"},{"description":"The contract does not state a path to terminate for material breach.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no for-cause termination)"},"explanation":"Without a for-cause termination path, parties must rely on common-law material-breach doctrines, which are jurisdiction-dependent.","id":"TERM-002-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-002","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No termination-for-cause clause detected"},{"description":"The contract does not state what happens upon termination.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no effect-of-termination clause)"},"explanation":"An effect-of-termination clause spells out the rights and obligations that survive, the return or destruction of materials, and the wind-down rules.","id":"TERM-005-s1-0","rule_id":"TERM-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"warning","source_citations":[],"title":"No effect-of-termination clause detected"},{"description":"No vulnerability-disclosure / coordinated-disclosure / bug-bounty policy reference was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"A documented disclosure pathway materially reduces the time-to-fix for vulnerabilities reported by researchers.","id":"ADDENDA-005-s1-0","recommendation":"Reference a vulnerability-disclosure policy (e.g., 'Vendor maintains a coordinated vulnerability disclosure policy and acknowledges reports within 5 business days.').","rule_id":"ADDENDA-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-sp-800-53-consensus-practice-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST SP 800-53 (consensus practice)","source_url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final"}],"title":"Vulnerability-disclosure handling missing"},{"description":"No reference to a secure-development-lifecycle (SDLC), SAST/DAST, or code-review program was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"An SDLC program is the practitioner-accepted way to ensure vulnerabilities are caught before code reaches production.","id":"ADDENDA-006-s1-0","recommendation":"Reference: e.g., 'Vendor maintains a secure-development-lifecycle program including SAST, DAST, and peer code review prior to production deployment.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-006","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-sp-800-53-consensus-practice-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST SP 800-53 (consensus practice)","source_url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final"}],"title":"SDLC reference missing"},{"description":"No data-classification / tiering / sensitivity-labeling scheme was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Without classification, all Customer Data is implicitly treated at the same (often lower) tier.","id":"ADDENDA-007-s1-0","recommendation":"Add: e.g., 'Customer Data containing personal data is classified as Confidential and receives the controls in Schedule X.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-007","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-sp-800-53-consensus-practice-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST SP 800-53 (consensus practice)","source_url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final"}],"title":"Data-classification mapping missing"},{"description":"No penetration-testing cadence was found.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(clause absent from the document)"},"explanation":"Annual third-party pen tests are the practitioner-accepted baseline for SaaS.","id":"ADDENDA-009-s1-0","recommendation":"State the cadence: e.g., 'Vendor commissions an independent penetration test at least annually and remediates critical findings within 30 days.'","rule_id":"ADDENDA-009","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"addenda-nist-sp-800-53-consensus-practice-","license":"Public domain or regulator re-use","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-12T00:00:00Z","source":"NIST SP 800-53 (consensus practice)","source_url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final"}],"title":"Penetration-test cadence missing"},{"description":"The document does not state where disputes must be brought.","document_position":0,"excerpt":{"end_offset":0,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":0,"text":"(no venue clause)"},"explanation":"Without a venue clause, default venue rules apply (in federal court, 28 U.S.C. § 1391). A clear forum-selection clause avoids ambiguity.","id":"CHOICE-003-s1-0","rule_id":"CHOICE-003","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[{"id":"stat-28-usc-1391","license":"Public domain (US government work)","license_url":"https://www.usa.gov/government-works","retrieved_at":"2026-05-11T00:00:00Z","source":"28 U.S.C. § 1391 (venue generally)","source_url":"https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/28/1391"}],"title":"No venue / forum clause detected"},{"description":"The contract references data but does not separately allocate data ownership.","document_position":545,"excerpt":{"end_offset":558,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":545,"text":"This Vendor Security Addendum (\"Addendum\") is entered into as of April 1, 2026, by and between Acme Corp, a Delaware corporation (\"Customer\"), and Globex Solutions Inc., a California corporation (\"Vendor\"), and is incorporated into and made"},"explanation":"IP and data ownership are different. For SaaS, the customer typically owns its data; the vendor typically owns usage analytics. Address each explicitly.","id":"IPDATA-004-s1-545","rule_id":"IPDATA-004","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Data ownership not separately addressed"},{"description":"Vendor shall not support TLS versions below 1. | Vendor shall not transfer Customer Data to any jurisdiction outside the agreed data-residency region without Customer's ","document_position":1651,"excerpt":{"end_offset":1698,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":1651,"text":"Vendor shall not support TLS versions below 1."},"explanation":"Negative covenants restrict what a party may do. Surfacing them collectively makes it easier to check they are intended and consistent with the overall deal.","id":"OBLI-005-s1-1651","rule_id":"OBLI-005","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Negative covenants: 2"},{"description":"cyber liability and data-breach insurance coverage of not less than Five Million Dollars ($5,000,000","document_position":6074,"excerpt":{"end_offset":6174,"section_id":"s1","start_offset":6074,"text":"10. Cyber Liability Insurance. During the term of the MSA and for two (2) years thereafter, Vendor shall maintain cyber liability and data-breach insurance coverage of not less than Five Million Dollars ($5,000,000) per occurrence. Upon request, Vendor shall provide Customer with a certificate of insurance evidencing t"},"explanation":"Insurance levels should match the deal size and risk. Common minimums are $1M per occurrence CGL and $2M E&O for services contracts.","id":"RISK-010-s1-6074","rule_id":"RISK-010","rule_version":"1.0.0","severity":"info","source_citations":[],"title":"Insurance requirements stated"}],"playbook_id":"vendor-security-addendum","playbook_match_confidence":1,"playbook_match_reasoning":"forced via sidecar to vendor-security-addendum","result_hash":"d0c010ce5f4e4aefec6d3efcbe9a3ff4e75a0bbd9b86cdd9118398e7d44a2a7b","source_file":{"name":"vendor-security-addendum-missing-pen-test-cadence-fail.txt","sha256":"19f5ead21ccfa0c6a3ab7f4f7881cdf3844c55bd0bcf784c72f5ce4be6a7bcaa","size_bytes":1},"version":"9.41.0"}